<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="476" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,392,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,371,392,418]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mandible with one or two small teeth apically, female mandible obliquely subtruncate; labrum nearly triangular or rectangular, apex rounded or truncate; face with definite scapal basin; eyes converging below, inner margins crenate and bowed out toward middle of frons; occipital carina complete to midventral line of head; mesoscutum sometimes curving rather sharply down to pronotum; omaulus present; episternal sulcus extending from subalar fossa to anteroventral region of pleuron, hypersternaulus and scrobal sulcus usually present; female foretarsus without a rake; fore wing with two submarginal cells, each submarginal cell receiving a recurrent vein; gaster with short petiole; female pygidial plate absent (
<bibRefCitation author="Bohart, R. M. &amp; Menke, A. S." box="[783,1048,608,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" refId="ref7690" refString="Bohart, R. M. &amp; Menke, A. S. (1976) Sphecid wasps of the world, a generic revision. University of California Press, Berkeley, Los Angeles and London, 695 pp." type="book" year="1976">Bohart &amp; Menke 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Menke, A. S. &amp; Vincent, D. L." box="[1062,1334,608,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" pagination="163 - 175" refId="ref7869" refString="Menke, A. S. &amp; Vincent, D. L. (1983) A review of the genus Polemistus in the New World (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). The Pan- Pacific Entomologist, 59, 163 - 175." type="journal article" year="1983">Menke &amp; Vincent 1983</bibRefCitation>
; Tsuneki 1992).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,392,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1892" box="[199,322,680,706]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,322,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Polemistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shuckard" authorityYear="1837" box="[375,513,680,706]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Passaloecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[375,513,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Passaloecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1835" box="[712,883,680,706]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pemphredonini">Pemphredonini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: forewing with three discoidal cells, well developed episternal sulcus, horizontal hypersternaulus (sometimes lacking in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,274,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Polemistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and absence of the female pygidial plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="476" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,392,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1892" box="[199,322,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,322,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Polemistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shuckard" authorityYear="1837" box="[486,624,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Passaloecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[486,624,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Passaloecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: inner orbits converging strongly below, omaulus present, midflagellar articles broader than long. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shuckard" authorityYear="1837" box="[991,1129,824,850]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Passaloecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[991,1129,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Passaloecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, inner orbits nearly parallel or at least not converging strongly below, omaulus rarely present, midflagellar articles longer than broad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
